Ganymede is Jupiter’s largest moon and also the largest moon in the solar system. Ganymede was discovered in 1610 by astronomer Galileo Galilei and is named for the mythical Greek son of a King who was carried to the sky by Zeus posing as an eagle.Sources:Image – http://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/cgi-bin/details.cgi?aid=11173Profile – http://solarsystem.nasa.gov/planets/ganymede, http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/factsheet/joviansatfact.html